-- Australia's Gillard Preparing for Election `Any Day Now,' News.com.au Says
-- Robert Fenner
-- 2010-07-11T05:37:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-11/australia-s-gillard-preparing-for-election-any-day-now-news-com-au-says.html

          
          
             Australian Prime Minister  Julia Gillard  is readying for an election with candidates in New South
Wales state holding a training session for a ballot that could
be called “any day now,” News.com.au reported  
 The Canberra office of Governor General  Quentin Bryce , who
can dissolve parliament to enable the election, is preparing for
Gillard to visit this week, News.com.au reported without saying
where it got the information.  
 Recent announcements by the prime minister on a proposed
mining tax, the processing of refugees and the future of an
emissions trading system are signs of preparation for a poll
that Gillard plans to hold this year, according to the website.  
 The prime minister is currently in Adelaide, in South
Australia state, where she is visiting her parents and meeting
Premier  Mike Rann .  
